1. Open the NRPE config on your EC2:

Bash
sudo vi /usr/local/nagios/etc/nrpe.cfg
Add a Command Alias:
Scroll down to the "COMMAND DEFINITIONS" section. You will see examples like command[check_load]. Add this line below them:

Bash
command[check_mem]=/usr/local/nagios/libexec/check_mem.pl -f -w 20 -c 10
(Note: Ensure the path to check_mem.pl matches where you installed it on the EC2 earlier.)

Restart NRPE:

Bash
sudo systemctl restart nrpe
2. Configure the CentOS "Master" (Local)
Now you need to tell your Nagios dashboard to actually request that "check_mem" command from the EC2 instance.

Open your remote host configuration:

Bash
sudo vi /usr/local/nagios/etc/objects/remote_host.cfg
Add the Memory Service:
Add this block below your "CPU Load" service:

Code snippet
define service {
    use                     generic-service
    host_name               AWS-EC2-Instance
    service_description     Remote Memory Usage
    check_command           check_nrpe!check_mem
}
Verify and Restart Nagios:

Bash
sudo /usr/local/nagios/bin/nagios -v /usr/local/nagios/etc/nagios.cfg
sudo systemctl restart nagios
